.TH "netlbl_unlhsh_netdev_handler" 9 "netlbl_unlhsh_netdev_handler" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
netlbl_unlhsh_netdev_handler \- Network device notification handler
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" netlbl_unlhsh_netdev_handler
.BI "(struct notifier_block *this "  ","
.BI "unsigned long event "  ","
.BI "void *ptr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "this" 12
notifier block
.IP "event" 12
the event
.IP "ptr" 12
the netdevice notifier info (cast to void)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Handle network device events, although at present all we care about is a
network device going away.  In the case of a device going away we clear any
related entries from the unlabeled connection hash table.
